The paper proposes a framework for causation discovery, which is a problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The framework involves partitioning variables and using causal solvers, which are techniques related to data mining (cs.DM) and statistical inference (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of conditional independence tests, which are a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
